# Arinda's Library â€” project memory

Personal Next.js 16 bookshelf app (Prisma + PostgreSQL). Display name: **Arinda's Library** (`APP_NAME` in `src/lib/constants.ts`).

## Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, Prisma 7, PostgreSQL, Tailwind, shadcn-style UI
- Read Next.js docs in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before changing framework code (non-standard APIs)
- Server actions: `experimental.serverActions.bodySizeLimit: "5mb"` in `next.config.ts`

## Local development

```bash
docker compose up -d postgres   # Postgres on host port 5433 (not 5432 â€” other project may use 5432)
cp .env.example .env
npm install
npm run db:migrate              # or db:migrate:deploy
npm run db:seed
npm run dev                     # http://localhost:3000
npm run test:book-search        # verifies Open Library + /api/books/search
```

## Environment variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL (local: `localhost:5433`) |
| `ADMIN_EMAIL` / `ADMIN_PASSWORD` | Optional admin login; **both must be set** to enable auth |
| `GOOGLE_BOOKS_API_KEY` | Not implemented yet; discussed as optional upgrade |

Auth: no DB users â€” env-only admin. Session cookie signed with email+password. Public paths: `/login`, `/api/health`, `/api/books/search`.

## Deployment

- **GHCR**: `.github/workflows/docker.yml` â†’ `ghcr.io/<owner>/<repo>:latest` on `main`
- **Compose prod**: `docker-compose.example.yml` + `.env.compose.example` (pull GHCR image + Postgres + `cover_uploads` volume)
- **Vercel**: see `DEPLOYMENT.md`; use cover **URLs** only (no persistent uploads)
- Migrations run at container start via `scripts/startup.ts`

## Features implemented

- Dashboard: stats, **monthly progress** chart (`src/lib/monthly-progress.ts`), genre chart, recent activity
- Library: grid, filters, local search (`?q=` â€” filters **collection only**, not Open Library)
- **Find & add book**: `LibraryBookSearch` on `/library` (outside Suspense) + lookup on `/library/new` (`AddBookForm`)
- Book CRUD, status, ratings, reviews, quotes, wishlist, collections
- **Cover upload**: `public/uploads/covers/` + URL; `src/lib/cover-upload.ts`; Docker volume `cover_uploads`

## Book search (Open Library)

- API: `GET /api/books/search?q=` â†’ `src/lib/book-search.ts`
- UI: `BookSearchAutocomplete` â€” debounced fetch from `onChange` (not only useEffect)
- Types: `src/lib/book-search-types.ts` (client-safe; do not import `cover-upload.ts` or `book-search.ts` in client components except types)
- Indonesian books: only if present in Open Library (e.g. "bumi manusia"); not full ID catalog
- Google Books API: free with quotas + API key; **not integrated** â€” better ID coverage if added later

## Client / server boundaries (important)

- `HeaderActions`, `SignOutButton` are **client** components (`"use client"`)
- Never import async server components into client nav (`TopNav`, `MobileHeader`)
- `showSignOut` passed from `(app)/layout.tsx` via `isAuthEnabled()`
- `LibraryBookSearch` must stay **outside** `<Suspense>` on library page so search hydrates reliably

